author: Reuters Editorial
title: Norwegian salmon export price fell to NOK 66.79 last week SSB
text:
OSLO, May 3 (Reuters) - The export price of fresh farmed Norwegian salmon fell to 66.79 Norwegian crowns ($8.25) per kilo last week from 67.32 crowns the previous week, Statistics Norway said on Thursday.
Volumes exported fell to 14,510 tonnes from 15,094 tonnes over the same period, it added.
Norway is the world’s largest producer of farmed salmon. The sector is the Nordic country’s second-largest export industry after oil and gas production.
Leading Norwegian producers include Marine Harvest, Salmar, Leroy Seafood, Grieg Seafood , Austevoll Seafood and Norway Royal Salmon . ($1 = 8.0966 Norwegian crowns) (Reporting by Oslo newsroom)
